HEADWORD: Semasiology
<hw>Se*ma`si*ol"o*gy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>shmasi`a</grk> signification + <ets>-logy</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Philol.)</fld> <def>The science of meanings or sense development
(of words); the explanation of the development and changes of the
meanings of words; -- more commonly referred to as
<altname>semantics</altname>.</def> --
